The body of a murdered man was yesterday found dumped near a chief’s office in Embu county. The man is believed to be a watchman. He had serious head injuries. The body was dumped in Kangaru village in Embu West subcounty. The deceased was not immediately identified, even by Thambo sublocation chief Rose Wambeti. She told the press she was called by residents who  informed her about the body. Wambeti said she called the police who arrived and started investigating. The assistant chief said the man could have been murdered elsewhere  and his body dumped at the scene. Wambeti said the body was discovered in the morning by residents. She said no villager could identify the man and urged any family with a missing person to report to the Embu police station. The body was moved to the Embu Level 5 Teaching and Referral Hospital mortuary.